quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  7,171,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We raised the mountain over them as if it were a cloud and they thought it would fall on them.¬†ňĻWe said,ňļ ‚ÄúHold firmly to that ňĻScriptureňļ which¬†We have given you and observe its teachings so perhaps you will become mindful ňĻof Godňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  7,172,"And ňĻrememberňļ when your Lord brought forth from the loins of the children of Adam their descendants and had them testify regarding themselves. ňĻGod asked,ňļ ‚ÄúAm I not your Lord?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúYes, You are! We testify.‚ÄĚ ňĻHe cautioned,ňļ ‚ÄúNow you have no right to say on Judgment Day, ‚ÄėWe were not aware of this.‚Äô"
  7,173,"Nor say, ‚ÄėIt was our forefathers who had associated others ňĻwith God in worshipňļ and we, as their descendants, followed in their footsteps. Will you then destroy us for the falsehood they invented?‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  7,174,"This is how We make our signs clear, so perhaps they will return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  7,175,"And relate to them ňĻO Prophetňļ the story of the one to whom We gave Our signs, but he abandoned them, so Satan took hold of him, and he became a deviant"
  7,176,"If We had willed, We would have elevated him with Our signs, but he clung to this life‚ÄĒfollowing his evil desires. His example is that of a dog: if you chase it away, it pants, and if you leave it, it ňĻstillňļ pants. This is the example of the people who deny Our signs.¬†So narrate ňĻto themňļ stories ňĻof the pastňļ, so perhaps they will reflect"
  7,177,What an evil example of those who denied Our signs! They ňĻonlyňļ wronged their own souls
  7,178,"Whoever God guides is truly guided. And whoever He leaves to stray, they are the ňĻtrueňļ losers"
  7,179,"Indeed, We have destined many jinn and humans for Hell. They have hearts they do not understand with, eyes they do not see with, and ears they do not hear with. They are like cattle. In fact, they are even less guided! Such ňĻpeopleňļ are ňĻentirelyňļ heedless"
  7,180,"God has the Most Beautiful Names. So call upon Him by them, and keep away from those who abuse His Names.¬†They will be punished for what they used to do"
  7,181,And among those We created is a group that guides with the truth and establishes justice accordingly
  7,182,"As for those who deny Our signs, We will gradually draw them to destruction in ways they cannot comprehend"
  7,183,"I ňĻonlyňļ delay their end for a while, but My planning is flawless"
  7,184,Have they not ever given it a thought? Their fellow man¬†is not insane. He is only sent with a clear warning
  7,185,"Have they ever reflected on the wonders of the heavens and the earth, and everything God has created, and that perhaps their end is near? So what message after this ňĻQuranňļ would they believe in"
  7,186,"Whoever God allows to stray, none can guide, leaving them to wander blindly in their defiance"
  7,187,"They ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ regarding the Hour, ‚ÄúWhen will it be?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúThat knowledge is only with my Lord. He alone will reveal it when the time comes. It is too tremendous for the heavens and the earth and will only take you by surprise.‚ÄĚ They ask you as if you had full knowledge of it. Say, ‚ÄúThat knowledge is only with God, but most people do not know.‚ÄĚ"
  7,188,"Say, ‚ÄúI have no power to benefit or protect myself, except by the Will of God. If I had known the unknown, I would have benefited myself enormously, and no harm would have ever touched me. I am only a warner and deliverer of good news for those who believe.‚ÄĚ"